Dionysius the Areopagite is the name given to the anonymous author of a
number of 5th century Christian texts. This mystical body of work was
influenced by Neoplatonism. Much admired during the Middle Ages and
Renaissance, debates about the identity of the author continue to this
day. These documents are from a very early stage in the development of
Christianity.

